TOPLEVEL DEZYNE README
**********************

BUILDING
========

Run
    ./configure
    make

Try
    make help

RUNNING
=======

Create fresh database and initialize 

    make database

Run dezyne server from the source tree

    make run
or
    webapp/server/main.js --debug --config=localhost

Run dezyne client from the source tree

    webapp/client/dzn

make sure to authenticate first

    make hello
or
    echo test | webapp/client/dzn -u test -s http://localhost:3000 hello

INSTALLING
==========

Install client in $HOME

    make client

PACKAGING AND DEPLOYMENT
========================

Run regression test

    make regression

Promote to blessed

    git fetch blessed # or git fetch origin
    git rebase blessed/master
    git push public
    make promote

If your $USER is not your verum user name (on git.oban), in .local.mk
add

    VERUM_USER:=<your verum user name>

In ~/.ssh/config, add something like

    Host buildmaster.oban
       User buildmaster
       IdentityFile ~/.ssh/buildmaster.id_rsa

Create tarball and executable shell archive

    make dezyne-server
